article.headline: Stetson 70, Campbell 51
article.story: DELAND, Fla. (AP) -- E.J. Gordon scored 17 points as Stetson handed Campbell its school-record 14th consecutive loss with a 70-51 win Monday night. Stetson (9-11, 7-6 Atlantic Sun Conference) won for the fifth time in its last seven games in a matchup of the Atlantic Sun's two lowest-scoring offenses. Campbell (2-17, 0-12) remained winless in league action. Anthony Register added 14 points for the Hatters while Djordjic Borislav finished with 10 points and eight rebounds. Gordon also had three steals to tie the school record of 156, set by Alexis McMillan from 2001-03. Stetson never trailed in the game and opened up a double-digit lead with a 14-0 run late in the first half. The Hatters were up 38-21 at the half and led by as many as 27 points. Colin Hunt had 11 points and was the only Campbell player in double figures. Campbell has lost its last 16 games played in Florida, including the last five times the Camels visited Stetson.
